String: Client: Rycharde (Sailors' Stay, Mhaura)Summary: Rycharde needs your help to find some dhalmel meat.
Client: Rycharde (Sailors' Stay, Mhaura)Summary: Rycharde needs your help finding some ingredients. He needs a beehive chip and some dhalmel meat.
Client: Rycharde (Sailors' Stay, Mhaura)Summary: Rycharde wants you to get him an ingredient called a puffball.
Client: Rycharde (Sailors' Stay, Mhaura)Summary: Rycharde wants you to deliver a dish to Valgeir in Selbina, and report on how he liked it.
Client: Take (Sailors' Stay, Mhaura)Summary: Take wants you to bring back one of Valgeir's dishes from Selbina.
Client: Rycharde (Sailors' Stay, Mhaura)Summary: Rycharde seeks an ingredient known as crawler's eggs.
Client: Rycharde (Sailors' Stay, Mhaura)Summary: Rycharde wants you to deliver a dish to Valgeir in Selbina, and report on how he liked it.
Client: Orlando (Orlando's Antiques, Mhaura)Summary: Find where the Goblins bury their junk. Bring back eight of the same type of junk and Orlando will reward you well.
Client: Celestina (Goldsmiths'  Guild Salesroom, Mhaura)Summary: Retrieve the sand charm Celestina's father carried. Your one clue: a sailor saw a pirate wearing it.
Client: Nereus (Sailors' Stay, Mhaura)Summary: Nereus seeks a dish of Gusgen clay from the depths of the Gusgen Mines.
Client: Vera (Outside Warehouse, Mhaura)Summary: Fulfill her request if you want the promised rewards.
Client: Katsunaga (Port Area, Mhaura)Summary: Bring Katsunaga a gugru tuna and he'll tell you all he knows about your fishing history.

Client: Lacia (In front of the Sailors' Stay, Mhaura)Summary: The Rhinostery has developed a new "mini" tuning fork of lightning. Ringing it upon the protocrystal in the Boyahda Tree will open the path to a one-on-one battle with the beast that awaits inside. However, only summoners are allowed to take up this challenge.
Client: Ripapa (In front of the Sailors' Stay, Mhaura)Summary: Ring the tuning fork of lightning upon the protocrystal in the Boyahda Tree. A path will open to the trial that awaits.

Client: Romeo (Atop Fishermen's Guild Salesroom, Selbina)Summary: Donate five pieces of onion equipment to help new recruits everywhere. Donors may receive an award.
Client: Oswald (Shepherd's Muster, Selbina)Summary: Oswald needs help retrieving his ring from the jaws of the ocean.

Client: Melyon (Weavers' Guild Salesroom, Selbina)Summary: Melyon will pay premium prices for any of the following: five heads of La Theine cabbage, three ears of millioncorn, one clump of Boyahda moss.
Client: Abelard (Mayor's Residence, Selbina)Summary: The mayor wants you to find stone monuments left by a certain adventurer and copy their writings to clay.
Client: Vuntar (Foot of Central Stairs, Selbina)Summary: Vuntar will pay premium price for rolanberries, but for only those that are thoroughly aged  and can serve as food for long voyages.
Client: Oswald (Shepherd's Muster, Selbina)Summary: Oswald wants to order something nutritious to cheer his girlfriend up a bit. Get him the special ingredient, a danceshroom.
Client: Oswald (Shepherd's Muster, Selbina)Summary: With his girlfriend still in the doldrums, Oswald wants to give her a pearl necklace. Find him a shall shell so he can make one.
Client: Thunder Hawk (Mayor's Residence, Selbina)Summary: Rescue two merchants from captivity. They should be somewhere in the Quadav camp in Beadeaux.
Client: Isacio (Waterfront, Selbina)Summary: You must prove yourself worthy before you can learn Isacio's fighting techniques.
Client: Devean (Behind Shepherd's Muster, Selbina)Summary: Find the pair of power sandals hidden in a jar somewhere in Davoi. Bring them back before time runs out for a cash prize.
Client: Zaldon (Fishermen's Guild Salesroom, Selbina)Summary: Some fish in Vana'diel like to eat shiny objects. If you catch one, let Zaldon cut it open for you.
Client: Fyi Chalmwoh (Goldsmiths'  Guild Salesroom, Mhaura)Summary: Fyi Chalmwoh wants to build a mannequin that rivals those of times past. It's your job to gather information on how to make one.

Client: Keshab-Menjab (Outside Orlando's Antiques, Mhaura)Summary: You've been asked to help bring in cleanly snapped rods for recycling. The recycled rods are supposedly sold somewhere around Bibiki Bay.
Client: Diederik (Port, Selbina)Summary: Diederik has lost a painting ordered by a valued customer. He wants you to help him earn time or get a new painting before anyone notices.

Client: Carbuncle (La Theine Plateau)Summary: Carbuncle wants you to visit all the protocrystals and gather the elemental energy of the sleeping gods. Will their imminent awakening mean fortune or doom for Vana'diel? Only Carbuncle's ancient friend at the Full Moon Fountain may know...

Client: Prof. Schultz (Xarcabard)Summary: What will be the first and final assignment given to you by Gunther Schultz II, the legendary reformer of military strategy? Your rite of passage begins by obtaining a scholar's testimony...

Client: Suspicious Hume (Pashhow Marshlands)Summary: You can expand the horizons of your soul, and it all begins by bringing either a rabbit hide, lizard tail, or two-leaf mandragora bud to one of the oddly accented and suspicious personages in Northern San d'Oria, Port Bastok, or Port Windurst.
Client: Kupofried (Walk of Echoes)Summary: Certain arcane powers known as "weapon skills" in adventurer vernacular can supposedly be harbored in one's body through the use of moogle magic.
Client: Kupofried (Walk of Echoes)Summary: Certain arcane powers known as "weapon skills" in adventurer vernacular can supposedly be harbored in one's body through the use of moogle magic.

Client: Quelveuiat (Altar of the Dawn, Tavnazia)Summary: Your initiation into the Tavnazian order of knights requires you to assess the situation from the lookout platform in the south of Lufaise Meadows.
Client: Despachiaire (Elders' Quarters, Tavnazia)Summary: Despachiaire has asked you to investigate the Mithran Tracker who has come looking for Cardinal Mildaurion.

Client: Frescheque (Third floor, Tavnazian Safehold)Summary: Try to find some information on the fate of a little girl who was kidnapped in a forest near the safehold. Her father says that she was wearing a tiny wristlet that is similar to her mother's.

Client: Anteurephiaux (First Floor, Tavnazian Safehold)Summary: You've been asked to travel to the Tavnazian coastline and find a rare shell carried by a monster-- preferably a "spirally" one that makes sound when you blow into it.
Client: Nivorajean (Second floor, Tavnazian Safehold)Summary: To complete a map of the Sacrarium, Nivorajean needs you to find a piece of the old floorplans.
Client: Epinolle (Third floor, Tavnazian Safehold)Summary: Epinolle wants you to find and bring back a Goblin that has left for Cape Riverne to make a map of the area.

Client: Travonce (Tributary, Tavnazian Safehold)Summary: Travonce's final wish before he dies is to reel in "the big one." However, your services are required to protect him from the monsters that lurk below the calm waters of Lufaise Meadows.

Client: Ferchinne (Tributary, Tavnazian Safehold)Summary: "A noble bird that walks on four legs. A proud beast that has the wings of an eagle." No, this is not a riddle; it is a description of the beast from which you must retrieve two tailfeathers.
Client: Elysia (Second Floor, Tavnazian Safehold)Summary: Find and bring back the hairpin that Elysia dropped while doing her shopping.

Client: Jonette (Tributary, Tavnazian Safehold)Summary: Jonette's dream is to revitalize the safehold's children by serving them an array of traditional Tavnazian dishes. However, she needs a cookbook to fulfill that dream.
Client: Ondieulix (Main Entrance, Tavnazian Safehold)Summary: You have been asked to find a rare plant that is often used in medicines. It supposedly grows somewhere on the Lufaise Meadows.
Client: Despachiaire (Elders' Quarters, Tavnazia)Summary: Despachiaire has asked you to investigate the origin of his late wife's amulet.
Client: Yurim (First Floor, Tavnazia)Summary: Yurim wants to show you the fruits of her research, but lacks the materials to begin the final stage of the experiment. You know what you have to do!

Client: Enaremand (Third floor, Tavnazian Safehold)Summary: One last material is required to complete Enaremand's final masterpiece. Perhaps the mannequin craftswoman in Mhaura has some clues to where you may be able to find it.

Client: Enaremand (Third floor, Tavnazian Safehold)Summary: Enaremand's final masterpiece is complete, but not as complete as he would like. The troubled mannequin craftsman has now asked you to help him find a necromancer in order to breathe life into his creation...
Client: ??? (Stone Monument, Riverne - Site #A01)Summary: A mysterious figure has requested your help repairing an old bell damaged in the recent earthquakes.
Client: Tressia (Patrol HQ, Tavnazian Safehold)Summary: Search for information regarding what happened on the day Wazozo's treasure was stolen.
Client: Justinius (Patrol HQ, Tavnazian Safehold)Summary: You have been asked to expel the black-robed intruders lurking around Monarch Linn.
Client: Despachiaire (Elders' Quarters, Tavnazia)Summary: A letter from Shikaree X addressed to you has arrived in the safehold. It appears she wants to gauge your battle prowess in Boneyard Gully.
Client: Despachiaire (Elders' Quarters, Tavnazia)Summary: A letter from Shikaree Y addressed to you has arrived in the safehold. It appears you have been challenged to a duel in Boneyard Gully.

Client: Owain (Main Entrance, Tavnazian Safehold)Summary: Reports suggest that planar rifts have materialized in Lufaise Meadows, the Misareaux Coast, the Uleguerand Range, and Attohwa Chasm. Engage and exterminate any interdimensional threats you may face.

Client: Owain (Main Entrance, Tavnazian Safehold)Summary: Word has it that planar rifts have arisen in Bibiki Bay, and that the dauntless Prishe has set out to put a stop to them. Get there first and exterminate all the interdimensional beasties you find!
Client: Buffalostalker Dodzbraz (Uleguerand Range)Summary: Dodzbraz is an Orc that despises snolls. If you bring him two "cluster cores," Dodzbraz will give you something useful to use against them.
Client: Anguenet (Carpenters' Landing)Summary: If you give a "muddy siredon" to the Tonberry that stands beside Anguenet, he will make you one of the Mithra's favorite foods.

Client: Koblakiq (Oldton Movalpolos)Summary: Koblakiq has stopped receiving letters from her brother Zeelozok after he went to speak with the Orcish overlord in Davoi. Koblakiq wants you to go there and search for him.
Client: Koblakiq (Oldton Movalpolos)Summary: A letter has arrived from Zeelozok asking for an "arnica root" to be brought to Castle Oztroja. Koblakiq has entrusted this task to you...

Client: Koblakiq (Oldton Movalpolos)Summary: Zeelozok has set out on a journey to destroy the Kindred's Divinity of Darkness. Koblakiq wants you to find her a "Demon pen" so she can learn more about their demon adversaries.
Client: Moogle (Mog House)Summary: Your moogle wants to take a power bow and a beetle ring to his family for the holidays. He sure would be happy if you found them for him.
Client: Moogle (Mog House)Summary: Your moogle wants to take a shrimp lure and some Selbina butter back home. He sure would be happy if you found them for him.
Client: Moogle (Mog House)Summary: Your moogle wants to take a raptor mantle and a wool hat to his friends in the Outlands. He sure would be happy if you found them for him.

Client: Loo Kohor (Monastic Cavern)Summary: Yagudo messenger Loo Kohor needs to deliver an important message. However, he cannot proceed, as he is attacked every time he sets foot in the Monastic Cavern. Your job is to take the missive and place it where the Overlord is sure to find it.

Client: Raptorlegs Gedwad (Qulun Dome)Summary: Gedwad has orders to sneak into the Qulun Dome and gather info on the Quadav's defenses. However, he is stuck at the entrance. Your job is to take Gedwad's seeker bats and place them somewhere they can spy on the Adamantking.

Client: Hooknox (Altar Room)Summary: Hooknox's plan to steal treasure from the Yagudo vault falls through when her disguise becomes too itchy. Your job is to take the key Hooknox swiped and use it to collect the riches...without being discovered by the Yagudo guards.

Client: Gu'Zho Thunderblade (Oldton Movalpolos)Summary: Gu'Zho has traveled to Movalpolos to become a mercenary. However, he cannot find the box to submit his application. Your job is to take Gu'Zho's letter to the box and lead the Goblin serjeant back to where Thunderblade will be waiting.

Summary: You have officially taken your first step down the road to fame with the Adventurers' Mutual Aid Network's new system: Records of Eminence. Now go clear some objectives and show Vana'diel your true worth!
Summary: Fight for the glory of your Unity leader under this new system established by the Adventurers' Mutual Aid Network!
Client: Green Thumb Moogle (Mog Garden)Summary: Peek inside the basket that rests at the end of the Mog Garden furrow.
Client: Green Thumb Moogle (Mog Garden)Summary: Look around the grove of trees in the Mog Garden.
Client: Green Thumb Moogle (Mog Garden)Summary: Examine the large boulder in the Mog Garden.
Client: Green Thumb Moogle (Mog Garden)Summary: Test the waters of the Mog Garden pond.
Client: Green Thumb Moogle (Mog Garden)Summary: Haul in the net cast off the coast of the Mog Garden.
Client: Green Thumb Moogle (Mog Garden)Summary: Take a look at the basket near the Mog Garden furrow and sow a seed.
Client: Green Thumb Moogle (Mog Garden)Summary: Check what drifted in on the tide by examining a spot on the Mog Garden's coastline.

Client: Green Thumb Moogle (Mog Garden)Summary: The Green Thumb Moogle's friend, Monsieur Kupont, is coming to pay him a visit, and the vacationing visitor appreciates rare and beautiful shells. There simply has to be some original marine life in the Mog Garden...

Client: Green Thumb Moogle (Mog Garden)Summary: Now Monsieur Kupont's villainous friend Kupivolo is joining the fray in the Adoulin Islands. Placate this pernicious patron by acquiring some article of note within the Mog Garden.

Client: Green Thumb Moogle (Mog Garden)Summary: A mob of merry moogles has manifested in your Mog Garden. Stockpile the subsequent sundries so your grand guests can be properly pampered: a moat carp creel from the pond as well as a branch of gnatbane and a date from the furrows.

Client: Green Thumb Moogle (Mog Garden)Summary: The Great Kupellion has come to your Mog Garden to help cure the MHMU scholars' wibbly wobbly woozies. He will need drill calamary from the coastal fishing net, a calico comet from the pond, and a philosopher's stone from a mineral vein.

Client: Green Thumb Moogle (Mog Garden)Summary: Susuroon swears fearsome beasts are menacing the garden, and employed Chacharoon--a supposedly world-class bodyguard--to deal with the threat. For now, let the bodyguard's lamb roam free in the Mog Garden to lure these monsters in.

Client: Green Thumb Moogle (Mog Garden)Summary: The fearsome beasts in question are apparently a rare breed of crab that plagued the garden before. While Atelloune's research on them may yield helpful clues, all you can do is motivate the lamb by feeding it La Theine cabbage.

Client: Green Thumb Moogle (Mog Garden)Summary: Crabs have ambushed and killed Chacharoon's beloved lamb. He has decided not to waste the animal's life, and thus needs a spool of cotton thread to craft an item to bolster his defenses and honor his fallen friend.

Client: Susuroon (Mog Garden)Summary: Susuroon needs your help getting Chacharoon interested in the jingly. The young Qiqirn idolizes adventurer types, so try handing him a gold beastcoin to convince him of your worth.

Client: Susuroon (Mog Garden)Summary: Chacharoon's life savings have been pilfered by some uncouth savage, and Susuroon can't face the young one himself. Head toward the newly cultivated area via the path located near the boat to find him.

Client: Chacharoon (Mog Garden)Summary: Chacharoon has asked you to help rescue a sickly adamantoise hatchling that has washed up on the shore. According to Chacharoon's diagnosis, the turtle needs hot soup to recover. Gather 12 crayfish for the soup and trade them to the Green Thumb Moogle.

Client: Green Thumb Moogle (Mog Garden)Summary: While preparing to accommodate four creatures in the Mog Garden's rearing grounds, Chacharoon has suddenly found himself inundated with work. Concerned for his health, the Green Thumb Moogle has sent you to the Goblins' shop in Lower Jeuno to help him gather supplies.

Client: Green Thumb Moogle (Mog Garden)Summary: A mysterious troupe of wistful women has come to your Mog Garden. They seem to be interested in riding crabs. Assist them in their endeavor by cultivating seeds in your garden.
Client: Green Thumb Moogle (Mog Garden)Summary: The engimatic troupe is now interested in sheep. Help the Green Thumb moogle out by bringing him Grow-M-Good.
